The Legislature passed three laws in May regarding dangerous animals, says Gerardo Cardenas, spokesman for Gov. Rod Blagojevich. Owners could face prison if they allow a vicious dog to run loose, or if they have not enclosed, spayed or neutered an animal that injures or kills someone. Many observers believe Sudan has dug in against a U.N. deployment in the vast region because it fears the force will hunt down officials and government allies suspected of war crimes for atrocities against Darfur's ethnic Africans.
